title: Automate lead generation using LinkedIn and Email 👽
description:
Your sales funnels are starting to dry up, and searching for new leads feels like looking for a snow cone in the desert. (“At this point, I’d settle for an ice cube.”)

Meeting your sales goals is a top priority, but that doesn't seem possible when there aren’t any leads to convert.

What if there was a tool that could help you automate your lead generation, contact hundreds of prospects per week, and lighten your workload?

TL;DR
👉 Get in touch with up to 700 prospects per week on LinkedIn

👉 Retrieve the professional email addresses of prospects and send them automated outreach sequences

👉 Best for: Freelancers, small businesses, and lead gen agencies that want to save time while scaling their customer acquisition

Waalaxy is a tool that lets you use LinkedIn and email to automate lead generation and messaging, plus monitor your team’s performance.

description: POV: You are now in the mountains and the mountains are in you, kindling enthusiasm, making every nerve quiver and jolting life into every pore and cell! Uttarakhand welcomes you with open arms to come & sample their famed Himalayan hospitality.

繼「知道一半的事」、「如風」、「不完滿結束」後，Ahdee 的全新單曲繼續療癒人心。「浮光」由 Ahdee 親自作曲，並與填詞人 Oscar 首度合作，再加上合作無間的監製 Nick Wong ，一起譜寫這首充滿療癒力量的作品。

面對浩瀚的大自然，紛亂的世界、急促的變化，我們少不免遇到失望而默默墜入情緒的深淵。但只要我們不放棄，繼續游，一定會重新找到力量，向新一頁出發。

1-Hour Healing Music for Anxiety Relief, Remove Depression, Rest the Mind | STRESS RELIEF
description:
WELCOME TO STRESS RELIEF MUSIC CHANNEL 🎶

Here, you will get the best music and views that you want. To listen to our other relaxing music, check out the playlists on our homepage. We Hope this music is useful for you. Please comment, like, share and subscribe to the channel to get our latest content!

▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎

WHAT IS STRESS?

- Stress is how we react when we feel under pressure or threatened. It usually happens when we are in a situation that we don't feel we can manage or control.

WHEN WE EXPERIENCE STRESS, IT CAN BE AS:

• An individual, for example when you have lots of responsibilities that you are struggling to manage

• Part of a group, for example if your family is going through a difficult time, such as bereavement or financial problems

• A member of society, for example during natural disasters or events like the coronavirus pandemic

• If you feel stress as part of a bigger group, you may all experience it differently. This can happen even if the cause of your stress is the same.

▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎

WHEN IS STRESS A PROBLEM?

Sometimes, a small amount of stress can help us to complete tasks and feel more energised. But stress can become a problem when it lasts for a long time or is very intense. In some cases, stress can affect our physical and mental health.

- Acute stress happens within a few minutes to a few hours of an event. It lasts for a short period of time, usually less than a few weeks, and is very intense. It can happen after an upsetting or unexpected event. For example, this could be a sudden bereavement, assault or natural disaster.

- Chronic stress lasts for a long period of time or keeps coming back. You might experience this if you are under lots of pressure a lot of the time. You might also feel chronic stress if your day-to-day life is difficult, for example if you are a carer or if you live in poverty.

▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎

PHYSICAL SYMPTOMS OF STRESS INCLUDE:

• Aches and pains
• Chest pain or a feeling like your heart is racing
• Exhaustion or trouble sleeping
• Headaches, dizziness or shaking
• High blood pressure
• Muscle tension or jaw clenching
• Stomach or digestive problems
• Trouble having sex
• Weak immune system

STRESS CAN LEAD TO EMOTIONAL AND MENTAL SYMPTOMS LIKE:

• Anxiety or irritability
• Depression
• Panic attacks
• Sadness

OFTEN, PEOPLE WITH CHRONIC STRESS TRY TO MANAGE IT WITH UNHEALTHY BEHAVIORS, INCLUDING:

• Drinking alcohol too much or too often
• Gambling
• Overeating or developing an eating disorder
• Participating compulsively in sex, shopping or internet browsing
• Smoking
• Using drugs

▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎

WHAT ARE SOME STRATEGIES FOR STRESS RELIEF? 

You can’t avoid stress, but you can stop it from becoming overwhelming by practicing some daily strategies:

1.) Exercise when you feel symptoms of stress coming on. Even a short walk can boost your mood.

2.) At the end of each day, take a moment to think about what you’ve accomplished — not what you didn’t get done.

3.) Set goals for your day, week and month. Narrowing your view will help you feel more in control of the moment and long-term tasks.

▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎▪︎

WHAT ARE SOME WAYS TO PREVENT STRESS?

1.) Try relaxation activities, such as meditation, yoga, tai chi, breathing exercises and muscle relaxation. Programs are available online, in smartphone apps, and at many gyms and community centers.

2.) Take good care of your body each day. Eating right, exercising and getting enough sleep help your body handle stress much better.

3.) Stay positive and practice gratitude, acknowledging the good parts of your day or life.

4.) Accept that you can’t control everything. Find ways to let go of worry about situations you cannot change.

5.) Learn to say “no” to additional responsibilities when you are too busy or stressed.

6.) Stay connected with people who keep you calm, make you happy, provide emotional support and help you with practical things. A friend, family member or neighbor can become a good listener or share responsibilities so that stress doesn’t become overwhelming.

Peace & Blessings! ♥︎

The giveaway is only open to the first 10,000 followers of the Marlin Madness YouTube channel. The winner will be chosen by random draw from among the first 10,000 followers.

The winner and their guests must provide proof of passport and any necessary travel visas prior to the start of the trip.

✥ Biển Của Hy Vọng (Sea of Hope Việt Nam) là chương trình truyền hình thực tế kết hợp âm nhạc, lần đầu tiên được Viettel Media mua bản quyền và sản xuất tại Việt Nam.

Từ sự thành công của Sea of Hope Hàn Quốc, Biển Của Hy Vọng đang nhận được sự mong đợi của hàng triệu các khán giả Việt. Hồi 2 của chương trình sẽ tiếp tục tại Cù Lao Mái Nhà - Phú Yên với những nhân vật mới, câu chuyện mới

✪ Ca sĩ Đông Nhi

✪ Ca sĩ Hòa Minzy
✪ Ca sĩ Đức Phúc
✪ Ca sĩ Quân A.P

Presenting #Bekhabar by #AdvaitSawant and #HridayGattani with lyrics by #DeepakYadav !

Bekhabar is a foot-tapping pop-genre song that carries emotional weight and taps your heart’s gloominess.  It tells the story of an unrequited love that still has hope.

title: Grita - Iván Troyano X Lenny Martinez
description:
Lenny Martinez y yo trabajamos juntos en esta canción allá por el 2005 junto a nuestro queridísimo Yadam González. Con el tiempo nos dedicamos a hacer otros proyectos y la canción se quedó esperando su momento.

En 2009 volví a hacer algunos arreglos con los productores Lupion y Dan Silva. Cambié melodías y cambié varias cosas de la letra.

El destino quiso que esta canción tan especial esperara su momento y estos últimos años la humanidad está pasando por miles de cosas horribles, que a su vez me han dado la fuerza e inspiración para lanzar esta canción. 

Letra: 

Este mundo que siente como se le apaga la voz
se queda ciego ante el dolor y la mentira entre los inocentes.
Mientras niños entienden que no hay nada para comer,
yo nunca llego a la razón a cada paso de un poder ausente y dice

Grita, grita
y haz que suenen tus palabras,
que se escuchen en las almas
que no hay verdad más fuerte que tú.

Oh yeah!

Quiero ver a mi gente poniendo todo el corazón.
Hagamos real esa ilusión y vivamos el presente.
Es increíble ver que hayan guerras por dinero
y ahora le canto a la vida y también quiero que cantes tú conmigo

Grita, grita (Grita, grita)
y haz que suenen tus palabras,
que se escuchen en las almas (que se escuche)
que no hay verdad más fuerte que tú. (No hay verdad más fuerte)

Grita, grita
y haz que suenen tus palabras,
que se escuchen en las almas
que no hay verdad más fuerte que tú.

Tú gritas, yo grito y grita aquel niño.
Que le regalen solo un beso
Que le regalen un poquitico de las nubes,
muchas flores pa acostarse en mil colores.
Yo grito y tú gritas y grita aquella madre que le duele perder la fe,
pero es difícil mantener la fe, en este frío mundo ¡vamos grita!

Podemos respirar y soportar la lluvia, 
tormenta que se irá en busca de otra luna.
Ya no habrá soledad y abrirás tu corazón,
Si este mundo pide paz haz que se pueda escuchar.

Grita, grita
aunque lloren tus palabras
que se escuche allí en tu alma
que no hay verdad más fuerte que tú.

Grita, grita (grita)
y haz que suenen tus palabras,
que se escuchen en las almas (que se escuche)
que no hay verdad más fuerte que tú. (no hay verdad más fuerte)

y que suenen tus palabras,
que se escuchen en las almas

description:

Prabhuva Ne Vatsalyam is a song remembering his Eternal Grace, Steadfast Love and his Compassion towards us. As it is written in the book of Lamentations 3: 22-23 (22.Because of the LORD’s great love we are not consumed, for his compassions never fail. 23.They are new every morning; great is your faithfulness.) And Vadda Gorrepilla is a song explaining about the Power in the blood of Jesus that it can wipe all our sins.

ప్రభూవా నీ వాత్యల్యం మా యెడల

title: Gukesh D vs Vladimir Kramnik, Nodirbek Abdusattorov vs Parham Maghsoodloo | Day 6 Armageddon
description:
Welcome to the most star-spangled showdown in the Armageddon Championship Series: Asia & Oceania featuring Vladimir Kramnik, Gukesh D, Yangyi Yu, Nodirbek Abdusattorov, Daniil Dubov, Vidit Gujrathi, Karthikeyan Murali, and Parham Maghsoodloo.

Tune in live on April 7 at 20:00 CET for chess heroes under intense time pressure with a real-time heartbeat and calorie-burned level as they race across the board for the chance to win €50,000 and two spots in Grand Finale. 

Commentators GM Jan Gustafsson and IM Jovanka Houska will do their best to keep up.

Armageddon Championship Series is a season of ultra-fast blitz tournaments with continental qualifiers and a Grand Finale event. The Series consists of seven-day double-elimination tournaments (if a player loses a match, he or she can still win the tournament and is eliminated after a second loss). Matches consist of two blitz games (3 minutes plus a 2-second move increment) and, if necessary, an Armageddon (5 minutes for White, 4 minutes for Black). There are two matches per day. The top two players of each event secure two places in the Grand Finale. All games are broadcast live from the Armageddon Studio in Berlin, and the total event prize fund of the Series is €460 000. The Series is organized by World Chess.

當詩人遇見他的音符

微醺的海遇見了月光 
勾起靈魂裡那份難得
吳青峰譜曲之作再一首推薦

#吳青峰
#最難的是相遇
#吳青峰16葉

這是一首令人無法隻腳站定，只能深深跌入的歌。詩人李格弟的歌詞，將微醺的念念想想，搖晃成氣味濃烈的子夜，青峰譜寫的旋律綿延迷離，讓偶遇不成也不散的醇香，盡留月光裡。編曲經過混音後，像緩慢搖擺浪花，輕輕晃入耳窩。一艘被歌聲沾濕的紙船，闖入靈魂的航線，十字星的聲波，消失在最遠的海面。

MV由 2014年許茹芸版的原班人馬齊聚：導演黃中平、男主角莫子儀，再加上〈費洛蒙小姐〉陳雪甄。導演延續了一場浪漫的故事，從2014年版本內的書本《仙人掌旅館》開始，在2020的青峰版本，男主角終於遇見了那位書中的女主角......莫子儀與陳雪甄兩人以極致的演技，在MV拍攝現場表達出無聲卻澎湃湧動的情感；兩人分別出演畫中肖像與石膏雕像的角色，雖然意識與身體被困在有形限制之中，但靈魂卻從未放棄尋找對方。

而他在一旁，寂寞而幸福地唱著。
你，寂寞而幸福地聽著。
 
最難的是相遇；最難得的，也是相遇。

-

〈最難的是相遇〉

一片濃濃酒意
像潛水到深深海底
水平面下的暈眩狂喜
從指間開始擴散

子夜心虛情怯
一杯濃艷冷冽
無法控制的迷離燦爛
從眼底開始氾濫

因為多麼難得是我
因為更難得更不可遇是你
可是相信我
最難的最難的  是相遇

今夜我的靈魂裡
有那一整座海啊
那一整個海正在微醺搖擺
因為遇見的你

今天晚上整個晚上
那整個微醺的海啊
當整個微醺的海遇見了月光
我就遇見了你

難得的是我
更難得更不可遇是你
可是相信我
最難的最難的  是相遇

title: Paid NASA Horizontal
Evolution of super heroes: Sharad Devarajan at TEDxGateway 2013
description:
Sharad is a creator (and an avid TED attendee), media entrepreneur, professor and self-professed comic book geek who wants you to break some rules and spark a creative renaissance in India.


His new company, Graphic India, is the culmination of his lifelong dream to launch characters, heroes and stories that tap into the unique creativity and culture of India but appeal to audiences worldwide. In the same way the West has created superheroes or Japan launched anime, Graphic India is transforming the perception of India in animation from being an 'outsourcer" to being 'the source.'


Sharad believes that great stories foster our imaginations and fuel our inspirations and the next Steven Spielberg, Hayao Miyazaki, JK Rowling or Stan Lee is sitting somewhere in India ready to change the world with the next great story.


Graphic's recent projects include 18 DAYS, a digital web series reimagining the Mahabharata with acclaimed Batman writer, Grant Morrison and Indian artist Jeevan J. Kang; and CHAKRA THE INVINCIBLE, an Indian superhero Sharad co-created with legend, Stan Lee (co-creator of Spider-Man, Iron Man, Hulk, The Avengers)


In addition to Graphic India, Sharad is an Adjunct Professor at Columbia Business School, and was previously the Co-Founder and CEO of Virgin Comics a company he co-founded, with Sir Richard Branson, authors Deepak Chopra, Gotham Chopra and filmmaker Shekhar Kapur.


Sharad was also the co-creator of the acclaimed, 'Spider-Man: India' comic series from Marvel. Where Spider-Man was reinvented as an Indian boy growing up in Mumbai, as "Peter Parker" became "Pavitr Prabhakar."

title: ADVOGADO DÁ DICAS EM SEGURO DE RESPONSABILIDADE CIVIL l Panorama do Seguro #161
description:
A 161ª edição do programa Panorama do Seguro aborda o Seguro de Responsabilidade Civil. Como convidado, Carlos Josias Menna de Oliveira, Advogado sócio da C. Josias & Ferrer Advogados Associados. Apresentada por Paulo Alexandre, a atração conta com a participação do Consultor Econômico do Sindseg SP, Francisco Galiza.

No primeiro momento, Josias falou sobre a evolução do seguro de RC nos últimos anos. “O ramo de responsabilidade civil, provavelmente, é o que tem o maior número de modalidades de contratações. Nós temos o RC de todos os gêneros hoje em dia, desde auto (RCF) até condomínio, o profissional, que tem sido o mais comercializado e alertado, esse é um seguro bastante difícil de fazer uma regulação perfeita, pois ele traz uma indagação constrangedora, pois o profissional precisa reconhecer sua culpabilidade e isso tem tornado as regulações mais difíceis”, explicou.

Já no segundo momento, o advogado falou sobre o RC na comercialização de produtos de internet. “Essa é uma situação a ser estudada com muito carinho também, pois a internet tem se prestado para muita vigarice, tem muitas empresas que oferecem produtos que não é aquele que é entregue, quando é entregue. E tem uma circunstância muito característica, as pessoas, em geral, confiam nas suas bandeiras, elas recebem aquele crédito de confiabilidade que lhe é emprestado, utilizam e esperam que as bandeiras tenham algum respaldo caso aconteça algo, sabemos que tem responsabilidade solidária, subsidiária, mas o fato é que isso macula a bandeira”, concluiu.

Apresentado pelo jornalista Paulo Alexandre e pelo consultor de economia Francisco Galiza, o programa tem três edições por mês e podem ser conferidas no link http://www.sindsegsp.org.br/site/sindsegsp-tv-video.aspx?id=4

Inscreva-se no canal da Sindseg SP: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCYFaNF60Ogx5j8cWsWRNECw

title: Kya Loge Tum | Akshay Kumar | Amyra Dastur | BPraak | Jaani | Arvindr Khaira | Zohrajabeen
description:
Desi Melodies presents in association with Cape Of Good Films & Azeem Dayani the first single, 'Kya Loge Tum,' from B Praak's highly anticipated debut album, "Zohrajabeen." The star-studded team of B Praak, Jaani, Arvindr Khaira, and Akshay Kumar reunites for the first time since the pop-culture-defining songs 'Filhall' and 'Filhaal 2.'

The emotionally charged lyrics written by Jaani, along with his heart-wrenching composition, add an extra layer of depth to the already powerful track produced by B Praak himself. Arvindr Khaira takes it to the next level with his visionary direction, featuring Akshay Kumar and Amyra Dastur's palpable chemistry that will leave you wanting more.

title: Critical Conversations: How to Bridge the Gap | Jennifer Edwards & Katie McCleary | TEDxGainesville
description:
NOTE FROM TED: This talk only represents the speakers’ personal views and understanding of the nervous system which lacks sufficient scientific support. We've flagged this talk because it falls outside the content guidelines TED gives TEDx organizers.  TEDx events are independently organized by volunteers. The guidelines we give TEDx organizers are described in more detail here: http://storage.ted.com/tedx/manuals/tedx_content_guidelines.pdf 

You spend large parts of your workday with people who do not share your generational background, values, way of doing things, and/or perspective. Rarely, can you do it all alone—create a great culture, improve employee and team satisfaction, or yield high engagement through collaboration efforts. All of us need meaningful relationships with diverse people because that is where innovation, growth, and everyday leadership expands. Communication experts Katie McCleary and Jennifer Edwards will equip you to have a curious, critical, and crucial conversation to bridge gaps between you and others.

Jennifer Edwards and Katie McCleary are passionate about creating healthy relationships between diverse people in a polarizing world. As Fortune 500 leadership and communication coaches, they equip people to engage in curious conversations that open up meaningful dialogue in even the most tense of encounters. Jennifer and Katie are “work wives” who personally know the transformative power of collaboration between diverse, talented, and smart people. They embrace their own dichotomies of being Conservative/Liberal; Country/Rock-n-Roll; Christian/Buddhist; Executive/Creative and have helped thousands find the sweet spot in their relationships by transforming how they show up, think, behave, and connect. Their work has appeared in Fast Company, Forbes, Wall Street Journal, Inc., NPR, New York Post, Shondaland, and ComputerWorld.

title: Here's why YOU HAVE to visit Nusa LEMBONGAN Bali in 2023
description:
Forget Bali - Come to Nusa Lembongan in 2023!
This is your list of things to do in Nusa Lembongan this year, your guide to what to prioritise and what to avoid
I have lived in Bali for nearly 3 years and this is my first ever time going over to Nusa Lembongan! But believe me, it will not be my last!!

We set off on the 9am ferry on Saturday morning arriving just before 10am, jumped straight onto a rented scooter (100k per day) 
We quickly found an awesome viewing platform of the beach you arrive in on which is simply stunning. What a welcome to paradise!
On our approach to the hotel we discovered the famous yellow bridge that links Nusa Lembongan to Ceningan (not whatever i said in the video haha) this landmark is a tourist attraction where travelers will stop and take photos but there is a dark history to this bridge...

After checking into the hotel we slipped next door to a local beach restaurant / bar which was super relaxing and such a nice way to spend the early afternoon before getting ready to see our friend for her birthday. 

In the morning was where the real fun starts, we first stopped off at the blue lagoon which was just simply stunning. I would strongly recommend coming early to avoid the crowds as this can get very busy. We then went for a lovely breakfast on the beach before heading over to The Devils Tear.. such an awesome spot!

蒼穹盛開的藍色花朵，
面具底下是難以捉摸；
即便向著刺也要伸手，
只為她笑容不為什麼。

「塔莉亞」是希臘九大繆思女神之ㄧ，手握「花與面具」。將充滿詩意的象徵元素作為歌曲創作靈感，敘述男孩仰望著如女神般心儀的她，就算明知這份美麗藏著危險與刺，也心甘情願為之臣服。

新生代最強唱作團體U:NUS，於《Reborn To be Alive》巡迴Showcase第二站 ── 台北，驚喜發表首支R&B全創作單曲《塔莉亞》（Thalia），透過精心編排的舞台表演與性感舞蹈，首度嘗試成熟魅力的表演風格，引起全場粉絲的熱烈迴響、陷入瘋狂。《塔莉亞》作為U:NUS發表的第三首作品，團員透過細膩的歌詞和與過往截然不同的曲風，展現更加純熟的唱腔與聲音表情，編曲元素更加入具千禧年代感性的電吉他solo與留聲機效果，加上男孩們如在耳邊溫柔呢喃的說唱，打造如同文藝愛情電影般的浪漫氛圍歌曲。

風格多變的U:NUS，再次突破了音樂創作的界限、為音樂之路添上嶄新色彩，也讓人更加期待未來他們將帶來什麼樣的驚喜！

title: Kolkata (praaner sohor) [official video] - Samudra feat. Priyanka Roy
description:
Samudra proudly presents the love towards the home city Kolkata..the city of joy. The city of culture, heritage, color, diversity and warmth. This foot tapping number was written by Piyali Majumdar Biswas and Sayantan Neogi, Shuvodip did a fantastic job with the arrangement, Priyanka did an amazing job with vocals along with Sayantan, and final audio, mix and master wrapped up by the incredibly talented Sound engineer Mrityunjoy Das in Crossfade studio. 
Avishek Chakraborty (Ronnie) have done an excellent job with the video, showing all the colors of the city have to offer. Three amazing dancers Rhea, Sudeshna and Meany presented three different dance forms which represented three different dimensions of the city. Anik, Sayantan and everyone of the team have done a tremendous job for this amazing little music video. 
Samudra thanks all the people associated with the production, the families and everyone out there who made this possible. Please watch the video, like, share and subscribe to the channel. Please support original music and spread love.
Hope you guys will enjoy this..cheers 😃

title: The Big Difference of being Little | Shivaay Kumar | TEDxRankalaLake
description:
Youngest on our TEDx Platform describing the significant impact of being little has, and can create. The Indian kid, based in Dubai holds the “World record” in reading 201 pages UPSIDE DOWN nonstop.
He has also entered India's book of records for reading the maximum number of words in a minute (208 words) and maximum books read upside down. He also holds Asia Book of Record of reading maximum number of books in 30 minutes Shivaay’s love and passion for reading started when he was mere three years old before he started school. The kindergartener (KG 1) is also a scholar in his academics and a star performer in mathematics and science Olympiad.
Other than reading, he loves outdoor games as well as indoor games. He enjoys word search and card games. His favorite subjects are mathematics, English, and science, and he has a deep interest in geography and the solar system. Kumar also has a YouTube channel on educational and fun videos called “litte_shivaay” to encourage other children in the same age group. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx

title: Surviving Ain’t Thriving – Break Free From The Herd | Chris Jarvis | TEDxDerryLondonderryStudio
description:
Chris Jarvis is known by many millionaire business owners and billionaire families as the guy who sees differently.

After 25 years of working with the super affluent, he discovered that there are countless ways to be successful, but only one path for each of us to find happiness and fulfillment.  

If you seek better health, increased wealth, stronger relationships, a deeper sense of purpose, or more fun in your life, then you want to find your “wild factor” to help you get unstuck, uncaged, and be free to Go Wild!  

If you are feeling uninspired, uncomfortable, or unfulfilled, then this talk may be the key to set you free to do what you were meant to do — without fear, guilt, or further hesitation.  

By the end of this talk, you will understand how a preoccupation with “surviving” sabotages our chances of “thriving” in our personal life and in our professional life.

Chris has enjoyed high highs and endured low lows.  Now he shares what he learned the hard way, helping seemingly happy and successful people escape the traps they set for themselves so they can find peace, laughter, and fulfillment. Chris’ greatest discovery came from years of hiking and a month on safari in Africa.  

The author of seventeen books and board member for a business school and medical school, Chris loves to teach.  He offers keynote speeches, strategy and innovation sessions, executive and team retreats, and “giraffe selling“ training program. With individual clients, Chris helps entrepreneurs and family offices handle their most complicated emotional and financial challenges to ensure successful transitions and exit strategies to generate greater leverage and more meaningful impact.  

Elevate Your Perspective.
See a Better Path.
Be the Giraffe. Chris Jarvis is known by many millionaire business owners and billionaire families as the guy who sees differently. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx

title: Differences between African Lions and Asian Lions
description:
Lions are majestic big cats that are found in various regions of the world. While all lions belong to the same species, Panthera leo, they are not all the same. African lions and Asian lions are two subspecies of lions that have a few differences in their physical characteristics, behavior, habitat, and conservation status. In this article, we will delve into the differences between African lions and Asian lions.

Physical Characteristics

The physical characteristics of African lions and Asian lions are different. The most significant difference is their size. African lions are generally larger and heavier than Asian lions. African male lions can weigh up to 550 pounds, while the largest Asian lions weigh around 400 pounds. The average height of African lions is around 4.5 feet, while the height of Asian lions is around 3.5 feet.

Another noticeable difference is their mane. African male lions have a long, dark mane that encircles their face, neck, and shoulders. The mane of an African lion can be a sign of strength and health. The darker and fuller the mane, the healthier and stronger the lion. In contrast, Asian male lions have a shorter and lighter-colored mane that doesn't cover their shoulders. The mane of an Asian lion is more like a fringe of hair around their neck.

Behavior

There are some differences in the behavior of African and Asian lions. African lions are known to be more social and live in larger prides than Asian lions. African lion prides can consist of up to 30 lions, while Asian lions usually live in smaller groups of around 10-15 lions. African lions are also more aggressive and territorial than Asian lions. They are known to defend their territory against intruders, including other lion prides, hyenas, and even humans.

Asian lions, on the other hand, are more solitary and territorial. They are known to have a smaller range than African lions and do not usually interact with other lion prides. Asian lions are also less aggressive than African lions, and they do not defend their territory as fiercely. This behavior may be due to the difference in prey availability in their habitats.

Habitat

African lions are found in sub-Saharan Africa, where they live in savannas, grasslands, and even some forested areas. They are not found in dense rainforests or deserts. African lions have a broad range across Africa and are found in several countries, including Tanzania, Kenya, South Africa, Botswana, and Namibia.

Asian lions, on the other hand, are found in a much smaller area. They are only found in the Gir Forest of Gujarat, India, and nowhere else in the world. The Gir Forest is a dry deciduous forest with a mix of grasslands, scrublands, and rocky hills. The habitat of Asian lions is much smaller and more fragmented than the habitat of African lions.

Conservation Status

Both African lions and Asian lions are listed as endangered species by the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN). However, their conservation status is slightly different. African lions are classified as vulnerable, while Asian lions are classified as endangered.
